tafsir[9]{c,v,t}:
  26,41,"(And when the wizards came they said unto Pharaoh: Will there surely be a reward for us if we are the winners) against Moses?"
  26,43,"(Moses said unto them) he said to the wizards: (Throw what ye are going to throw!"
  26,45,"(Then Moses threw his staff and lo! it swallowed that which they did falsely show) of wizardry."
  26,47,"(Crying: We believe in the Lord of the Worlds) upon which Pharaoh said: are you referring to me?"
  26,48,"They said: (The Lord of Moses and Aaron."
  26,51,"(Lo! we ardently hope that our Lord will forgive us our sins) our idolatry (because we are the first of the believers) in Moses."
  26,55,"(And lo! they are offenders against us) they have caused our fury and anger."
  26,58,"(And treasures) wealth (and a fair estate) beautiful houses."
  26,60,"(And they overtook them at sunrise."